What is Prototype Design Pattern?
Interview Definition

Prototype Design Pattern is a creational design pattern in which new objects are created by copying (cloning) an existing object instead of creating them from scratch.

Simple Definition

Instead of creating a new object from the beginning,

👉 copy an existing object.

Real-Life Analogy

Suppose a school has 100 identical ID cards.

Instead of designing every card from scratch,

The school creates one template and makes copies.

Original ID Card
        │
        ▼
 Copy 1
 Copy 2
 Copy 3
 Copy 4

Exactly the same idea.

Example
const person = {
    name: "Lucky",
    age: 22
};

const person2 = Object.create(person);

console.log(person2.name);

Output

Lucky

person2 inherits properties from person.

Why use it?

Instead of creating similar objects repeatedly,

create one prototype and reuse it.

Interview One-Liner

Prototype Pattern creates new objects by cloning an existing object rather than creating them from scratch.

